From: Michael Walle <michael@walle.cc>
Date: Thu, 28 Nov 2019 23:38:02 +0100
Subject: ASoC: fsl_sai: add IRQF_SHARED

Git-commit: 2eb2d314a80eb8bb1a6faf2a74321d4497e1687d
Patch-mainline: Queued
Git-repo: git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/next/linux-next.git
References: jsc#SLE-9316

The LS1028A SoC uses the same interrupt line for adjacent SAIs. Use
IRQF_SHARED to be able to use these SAIs simultaneously.

Signed-off-by: Michael Walle <michael@walle.cc>
Reviewed-by: Fabio Estevam <festevam@gmail.com>
Acked-by: Nicolin Chen <nicoleotsuka@gmail.com>
Acked-by: Daniel Baluta <daniel.baluta@nxp.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20191128223802.18228-1-michael@walle.cc
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Mian Yousaf Kaukab <yousaf.kaukab@suse.com>
---
 sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c
+++ b/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c
@@ -960,7 +960,8 @@ static int fsl_sai_probe(struct platform
 		return irq;
 	}
 
-	ret = devm_request_irq(&pdev->dev, irq, fsl_sai_isr, 0, np->name, sai);
+	ret = devm_request_irq(&pdev->dev, irq, fsl_sai_isr, IRQF_SHARED,
+			       np->name, sai);
 	if (ret) {
 		dev_err(&pdev->dev, "failed to claim irq %u\n", irq);
 		return ret;
